Durban - Four people were killed and another injured following a vehicle rollover in Pietermaritzburg on Sunday. According to ER 24 spokesperson, Russel Meiring the accident took place on Hopewell Road just after 6 pm. "On further inspection, paramedics found a light motor vehicle lying on its roof on the side of the road against a tree. "One person was found lying outside the vehicle while three others were found lying trapped inside the vehicle. "Paramedics assessed the patients and found that two men and two women had sustained numerous, fatal injuries. Nothing could be done for them and they were declared dead." Meiring said a fifth patient was assessed on scene and found to have sustained only minor injuries. The patient was treated and thereafter transported to a nearby hospital for further treatment. Meiring said SAPS were on scene. In a separate incident, three people were injured when their vehicle lost control and crashed into a wall on Bluff Road before Beacon Road just after 9 am on Monday morning. According to Garrith Jamieson on Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the driver still in the vehicle. "The driver and two passengers had sustained moderate injuries and were stabilised on the scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being transported to a nearby Hospital for the further care that they required." Daily News